1
00:00:52,110 --> 00:00:55,040
We've just received
some unbelievable news.

2
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:57,010
Serial killer Lee Woo Gyeom...

3
00:00:57,010 --> 00:00:59,920
who had captured national attention
and sparked heated debate...

4
00:01:00,180 --> 00:01:02,890
has saved a terminally ill patient.

5
00:01:06,860 --> 00:01:11,430
Following reports that patient Woo Jin,
has made a complete recovery,

6
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:16,100
the court will face greater difficulty
in its sentencing deliberations.

7
00:01:16,170 --> 00:01:17,330
(Prosecution Case Inquiry)

8
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:20,370
If you dig too deep into this,

9
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:24,470
you're the one who could get hurt.

10
00:01:24,540 --> 00:01:25,910
(Suspension of Indictment
for Insufficient Evidence)

11
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,980
(Regarding Shin Ho Chang's case)

12
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,310
A medical demonstration?

13
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,280
What kind of nonsense is this?

14
00:01:48,030 --> 00:01:49,670
Hey. Did you order food?

15
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,700
No, I didn't.

16
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:59,080
Who are you?

17
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:03,150
Hello. I...

18
00:02:03,410 --> 00:02:05,880
I'm Chae Jeong Su,
the chairman of Chaeum Medical Center.

19
00:02:24,930 --> 00:02:27,640
What brings you here?

20
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:33,280
First, I'd like to thank you.

21
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:35,450
What do you mean by that?

22
00:02:36,210 --> 00:02:39,550
Thanks to you, Mr. Park,
Lee Woo Gyeom's procedure was a success.

23
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:43,890
And the final verdict
will surely be in his favor.

24
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:46,860
This means patients ruined
by incurable diseases...

25
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:48,460
can finally receive treatment.

26
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:54,130
I only did my best for my client
as his attorney.

27
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:56,770
And the trial isn't even over yet.

28
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:01,200
How is your daughter doing?

29
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,440
Excuse me?

30
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,510
I saw it on the news.

31
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,420
Mr. Park.

32
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:19,120
Do you really think
the court will execute a man...

33
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,560
who saved a life?

34
00:03:22,260 --> 00:03:26,560
The National Assembly
can't ignore public opinion,

35
00:03:26,830 --> 00:03:29,070
and they'll eventually use Lee Woo Gyeom
to treat patients.

36
00:03:29,130 --> 00:03:31,800
So, how will they decide who gets treated?

37
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:34,770
For the sake of fairness, they'll
probably...

38
00:03:35,610 --> 00:03:37,270
use a lottery system, don't you think?

39
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,410
What are you getting at?

40
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,810
Chaeum will be...

41
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,050
the organization that makes the selection.

42
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:54,360
For patients who need urgent treatment,
like your daughter,

43
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:58,630
Chaeum wants to develop a cure
from Lee Woo Gyeom's blood.

44
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,130
To develop the cure,
could you be on our side...

45
00:04:01,660 --> 00:04:04,200
and persuade Lee Woo Gyeom?

46
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,510
For your daughter's sake.

47
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:58,650
(Achilles' Heel)

48
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:01,360
(Lee Woo Gyeom's demo
may cure the incurable.)

49
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:02,530
(Medical demo between prison and court)

50
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:03,590
(Components in Lee Woo Gyeom's blood
are key.)

51
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:05,160
(People call for
a steady supply of his blood.)

52
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,860
This is insane.

53
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,970
Public opinion,
which condemned Lee Woo Gyeom until now,

54
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:14,870
has swung over 30 percent in his favor.
People are so fickle.

55
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:15,940
It's understandable.

56
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,340
It was the lead story on foreign news too.

57
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:23,480
I wonder if Lee Woo Gyeom's cure
could get rid of this scar.

58
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,420
It drives me crazy
every time I look in the mirror.

59
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:28,220
Hey, look at this.

60
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:30,250
Look.

61
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,520
Isn't this hilarious?

62
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:35,160
People are going wild.

63
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,160
(Contains his power for reborn skin!)

64
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:40,860
But isn't that actually possible?

65
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:45,100
Totally. I mean,
they cured an incurable disease.

66
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:47,640
Wait a second.

67
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:51,170
Maybe I should make a business proposition
to Lee Woo Gyeom.

68
00:05:51,370 --> 00:05:52,810
What kind of business?

69
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:56,610
Developing a hair loss treatment.
With millions bald, if you made that,

70
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,950
you'd be sitting on a gold mine.

71
00:05:58,310 --> 00:05:59,520
Mr. Park, where are you going?

72
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,790
I'm going to check on Min Seo.

73
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,160
- Take care.
- Okay.

74
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:11,460
Hey, Mr. Park is so worried about Min Seo,
and you're... Seriously...

75
00:06:14,230 --> 00:06:15,400
It's Park Han Jun!

76
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:21,670
- How did you first meet Lee Woo Gyeom?
- What convinced you the cure was real?

77
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,810
Did you have a contingency plan
for the demonstration's failure?

78
00:06:23,910 --> 00:06:25,740
Gosh, what do you think you're doing?

79
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,440
I'll hold them off.
You need to get out of here, fast.

80
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:28,840
Hold on, wait a minute.

81
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:31,510
Hey, I'm the one who introduced
Mr. Park to Lee Woo Gyeom.

82
00:06:31,580 --> 00:06:33,250
- Head downstairs, quickly!
- Mr. Park!

83
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:34,780
- He called me back then, and...
- Mr. Park Han Jun!

84
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:36,990
- Just a moment!
- Hey, wait. Wait!

85
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:39,120
- Just one comment, please!
- Mr. Park!

86
00:06:39,990 --> 00:06:43,290
- All right. I know you're curious, but...
- Step back. You can't film this.

87
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:46,960
Come on, let's discuss this over coffee.
We're all colleagues, for crying out loud!

88
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:49,570
(National Assembly Member's Office)

89
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:57,040
What took you so long?

90
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:14,460
Prosecutor Cha.
What's the status of the trial?

91
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:18,090
Now, talk of the death penalty
is completely off the table for a while.

92
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,460
You'll just have to be patient.

93
00:07:21,930 --> 00:07:22,930
What was that?

94
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,130
The trial isn't over yet.

95
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,070
Are you playing word games with me?

96
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,080
Public opinion has completely swung
in his favor.

97
00:07:34,910 --> 00:07:37,980
Even if he gets the death penalty,
this isn't a win for us anymore.

98
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,950
I'm going to make this
a psychological battle.

99
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,390
Lee Woo Gyeom may have succeeded
with his cure,

100
00:07:43,450 --> 00:07:46,320
but people are still afraid
of potential side effects.

101
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,860
And that very fear...

102
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:49,660
is what I'm going to exploit.

103
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:53,600
So you have evidence to support that?

104
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:01,000
Director Oh. May I be excused?

105
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,770
I have a lot to prepare.

106
00:08:04,410 --> 00:08:07,880
- Sir...
- Fine, go! Just go!

107
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:09,450
Go!

108
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:14,380
Prepare quickly and perfectly. Got it?

109
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:18,290
And one more thing, Assemblyman.

110
00:08:21,490 --> 00:08:24,860
You keep saying, "We will win."
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

111
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:26,760
So allow me to set the record straight.

112
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:29,430
Weren't we supposed to be
strategic allies?

113
00:08:29,930 --> 00:08:32,800
The one who wins this trial is me. Not us.

114
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:36,740
You seem to be under a misconception.

115
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:39,880
I work for the Public Prosecutors' Office
of the Republic of Korea.

116
00:08:40,380 --> 00:08:42,380
I am not your subordinate.

117
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:46,180
From now on,
if you have any questions for me,

118
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:50,590
you are to come to my office. In person.

119
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:54,420
You will request an appointment
that accommodates my schedule,

120
00:08:54,590 --> 00:08:56,530
and then you may ask.
I would appreciate that.

121
00:08:56,830 --> 00:08:59,200
Now then. The trial is imminent,
so if you'll excuse me.

122
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:04,600
What? What did she... What was that?

123
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:08,770
Is she out of her mind? That...

124
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,870
Who does she think she is?

125
00:09:14,210 --> 00:09:15,410
(Courthouse)

126
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:18,750
He's a serial killer
who brutally murdered 17 people,

127
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,620
and the man who recently performed
a miraculous cure on a terminal patient.

128
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:24,450
Today is the final hearing
in the trial of Lee Woo Gyeom.

129
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:27,990
Experts remain sharply divided
on the matter.

130
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:32,360
Therefore, the court's stance on where
the public's best interests lie...

131
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:35,000
is expected to
heavily influence the verdict.

132
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:41,200
Meanwhile, massive crowds have gathered
in front of the courthouse.

133
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:44,240
There are those calling for
Lee Woo Gyeom's immediate execution,

134
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:48,040
facing off against a group
that worships him as a savior.

135
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:51,950
Police have deployed large forces
to prepare for any potential incidents,

136
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:54,380
and they are on high alert
for possible clashes.

137
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:57,920
For now, the demonstrations are limited
to chanting and picket signs,

138
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:01,420
but the tension at the scene
is growing by the minute.

139
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:16,810
(Justice is blind, but Woo Gyeom is not.)

140
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,710
(No one is above the law.)

141
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,450
Reporter Jo, you're here.

142
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,050
They haven't gone in yet, have they?

143
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,800
Prosecutor.

144
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:46,370
Proceed with your sentencing.

145
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:53,510
A few days ago,

146
00:10:53,810 --> 00:10:57,950
I met with Lee Chang Se, who was rescued
at the scene of the defendant's arrest,

147
00:10:58,550 --> 00:11:02,380
and Song Tae Jin,
the defendant's sixth patient.

148
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:11,860
Both men's health has rapidly worsened,
and their lives now hang in the balance.

149
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,060
Your Honor.

150
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:16,570
And yet, can we consider
the successful medical demonstration...

151
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:20,540
as definitive proof
of the defendant's healing abilities?

152
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:24,240
I submit that we must not only
re-examine the falsehoods...

153
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,740
in the evidence, witness accounts,
and testimonies...

154
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:29,910
concerning the defendant's cure,

155
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,350
but I also ask this court...

156
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:35,150
to conduct a full review
of his alleged healing ability.

157
00:11:36,020 --> 00:11:37,050
As in the original trial,

158
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,220
the prosecution seeks the death penalty.

159
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:55,570
Defense counsel.
Proceed with your closing argument.

160
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:07,380
Counselor?

161
00:12:11,890 --> 00:12:12,890
I apologize.

162
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:19,730
I...

163
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:25,000
If the defendant's cure is a fraud,
as the prosecution claims,

164
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:29,370
then I have no right
to make a closing argument here today.

165
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,450
Your Honor.

166
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:41,880
However, Mr. Song Tae Jin,

167
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,650
unlike the other patients
who made a full recovery,

168
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,320
did not believe in the effectiveness
of the defendant's treatment.

169
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:49,060
No, I wasn't cured.

170
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,090
I've started going back to the hospital.

171
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:56,530
He was concurrently taking
other prescribed medications.

172
00:12:57,570 --> 00:12:58,770
The same goes for Lee Chang Se.

173
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:03,070
Despite the defendant's repeated warnings
at the arrest scene, the police...

174
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:06,040
forcibly transferred him to a hospital.

175
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:11,780
If my treatment method
gets mixed with theirs,

176
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:13,580
he will never recover.

177
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:15,820
As a result, tragically,

178
00:13:16,190 --> 00:13:20,520
he is now critical due to side effects
from the medication. But none of this...

179
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:24,790
is a reason to deny
the defendant's ability to heal.

180
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:31,130
The prosecution continues
to ignore the truth,

181
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,240
and I find that deeply regrettable.

182
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,240
Your Honor.

183
00:13:38,370 --> 00:13:39,370
We all...

184
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:45,050
bore witness to that moving moment,
that deeply moving moment,

185
00:13:45,710 --> 00:13:47,580
of the defendant curing a young patient.

186
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:49,950
Some might say that,

187
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:53,020
the child was cured...

188
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:56,860
like a miracle in a fairy tale.

189
00:13:57,230 --> 00:14:00,860
But the defendant's cure is no fantasy,
no magic, and no miracle.

190
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,370
For patients with incurable diseases...

191
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,200
and their families,

192
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:09,940
it's what they have
desperately dreamed of...

193
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:11,940
made into reality.

194
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:18,380
It is the undeniable fact
that gives them a new lease on life.

195
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:20,650
Therefore, in this trial,

196
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:22,720
I ask for a sentence that allows him...

197
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:25,920
to serve patients suffering
from incurable diseases,

198
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:28,420
and in doing so, pay his debt to society.

199
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:33,660
I sincerely ask the court
for a wise and just sentence.

200
00:14:35,430 --> 00:14:38,470
Finally, to respect and protect
human dignity and value...

201
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:41,700
and the nobility of the human spirit,

202
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:44,840
is the very reason
we are in this courtroom,

203
00:14:45,770 --> 00:14:47,440
and I believe it is the very essence
of the law.

204
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,080
(Defendant)

205
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:56,420
That is all.

206
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:15,340
I will now deliver the sentence.

207
00:15:21,780 --> 00:15:26,620
The defendant is a brutal criminal
who took precious lives.

208
00:15:30,850 --> 00:15:32,320
However, the court...

209
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:36,490
while watching a child get treatment
at the hands of the defendant...

210
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:38,290
grappled with a difficult question.

211
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:43,070
Is condemning his hands the only true path
to justice?

212
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:47,740
We also considered the possibility...

213
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:52,310
that the number of lives
the defendant could save in the future...

214
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:54,210
might exceed the number he has taken.

215
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:56,580
Therefore, this court...

216
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:59,250
has determined that for the defendant,
punishment...

217
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:02,950
is to treat the sick
for the rest of his life...

218
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:06,260
and thus make a positive contribution
to society.

219
00:16:06,690 --> 00:16:08,490
The court sentences him as follows.

220
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,730
The defendant, Lee Woo Gyeom...

221
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,660
shall serve his sentence
in a state-approved quarantine facility...

222
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:20,270
by treating terminally ill patients.

223
00:16:21,570 --> 00:16:23,570
This is not an exemption from punishment.

224
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:27,440
It means he must spend his entire life
atoning.

225
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:29,710
If, for any reason,

226
00:16:30,210 --> 00:16:32,180
he refuses to perform these treatments,

227
00:16:32,710 --> 00:16:35,220
his original death sentence
will be reinstated.

228
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:37,990
This is a conditional death sentence.

229
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:02,780
- He's coming out.
- Prosecutor Cha!

230
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,950
Prosecutor, do you respect
the court's decision?

231
00:17:05,010 --> 00:17:07,250
Prosecutor Cha, why do you think
you lost the case?

232
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,750
Do you plan to file for a retrial?

233
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:11,820
Some say this prosecution was a reach
from the start. Your thoughts?

234
00:17:11,890 --> 00:17:14,190
- Do you agree with the verdict?
- Please, just give us a comment.

235
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:15,520
How are you feeling?

236
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:19,390
- You murdering jerk!
- Kill him!

237
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,430
Execute him!

238
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:38,010
With the Supreme Court ruling in favor of
Lee Woo Gyeom,

239
00:17:38,150 --> 00:17:40,920
all eyes are now on his next move.

240
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:46,420
He is to be held at Chaeum Medical Center,
a state-designated isolation facility,

241
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:50,590
which is the largest medical research
and treatment complex...

242
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,900
and is equipped with an elite medical team
and security force.

243
00:17:57,330 --> 00:18:01,940
Hello. I am Chae Jeong Su,
Chairman of the Chaeum Medical Group.

244
00:18:07,010 --> 00:18:10,250
What I wish to state today
on behalf of Chaeum...

245
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:14,920
stems from a single desire
to make our society healthier.

246
00:18:15,780 --> 00:18:18,320
In light of the recent trial,
we at Chaeum Medical Group...

247
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:21,060
will help Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom,
who received a conditional death sentence.

248
00:18:21,420 --> 00:18:24,290
We will donate a facility
so that he may focus on treating patients.

249
00:18:24,530 --> 00:18:28,430
And we pledge our unconditional support
for this endeavor.

250
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,560
(National Assembly Member's Office)

251
00:18:29,630 --> 00:18:33,070
The debate over Lee Woo Gyeom is spreading
throughout the political sphere.

252
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:37,470
While the government respects the ruling
as one considering public interest,

253
00:18:37,540 --> 00:18:40,410
the controversy over the legitimacy
of this new system...

254
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:44,410
shows no signs of dying down.

255
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,750
It's bad enough we're letting a murderer
off the hook.

256
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,590
- Now we have to build him a sanctuary?
- You heard the verdict.

257
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,720
What's the Ministry of Justice's
take on this?

258
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:57,990
We intend to respect
the honorable members' opinions.

259
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:03,100
This is for the good of the people anyway.
Let's just push it through.

260
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:07,100
Protecting a murderer?
How is that for the public good?

261
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:11,240
It's already been decided.
Let's not fight amongst ourselves.

262
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:14,180
For now, let's just discuss
how to select the patients.

263
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:15,680
Still, it only seems right
that the first treatment...

264
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,510
goes to the lawyer Park's daughter.

265
00:19:17,980 --> 00:19:19,380
It's only right, don't you think?

266
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:22,720
The lawyer's daughter...

267
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,250
Unbelievable.

268
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:29,620
(Guam district prosecutors' office)

269
00:19:30,090 --> 00:19:32,060
This is tough, isn't it?

270
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,230
No matter how I look at it, it's a mess.

271
00:19:37,530 --> 00:19:38,970
I'm talking about you, Prosecutor Cha.

272
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:41,600
Why do you have to make things
so complicated?

273
00:19:43,070 --> 00:19:44,070
I'm sorry, sir.

274
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:47,680
You know I'm not one
to fixate on the outcome, right?

275
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:50,550
But you handled this with such arrogance.

276
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:52,510
Do you think at my age...

277
00:19:53,050 --> 00:19:55,480
Do you really think I enjoy
sucking up to Assemblyman Baek?

278
00:19:56,180 --> 00:19:57,920
There are still unresolved cases
related to Lee Woo Gyeom...

279
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,790
You're being transferred
to Namhae next month.

280
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:01,460
What?

281
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:03,130
Why the surprise?

282
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:06,130
A serial killer gets to have
a bright future,

283
00:20:06,730 --> 00:20:08,630
so you think the prosecutor in charge
gets off scot-free?

284
00:20:16,870 --> 00:20:18,010
One hundred twenty-nine.

285
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,640
One hundred thirty.

286
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,810
Two hundred ninety-eight.

287
00:20:23,510 --> 00:20:24,680
Shoulder throw!

288
00:20:26,620 --> 00:20:30,020
Liver, liver! Heart, heart!

289
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,230
Hey, Min Gyeong.

290
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:44,730
What are you doing, Reporter Jo?

291
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:48,400
- What do you mean?
- That. How long have you been doing this?

292
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,540
Ever since I started at the Daehan Ilbo.

293
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:55,440
- Man, that's already been 20 years.
- Gosh! That's incredible!

294
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:58,780
It's nothing special, just something I do.
I just try to be consistent.

295
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:00,880
So why are you so dedicated to it?

296
00:21:01,620 --> 00:21:02,780
So I can write my articles.

297
00:21:03,490 --> 00:21:08,020
- What?
- Sound writing comes from a sound body.

298
00:21:09,420 --> 00:21:13,030
You should give it a try.
Learning this could really come in handy.

299
00:21:14,330 --> 00:21:16,160
Let's get you warmed up first
so you don't get hurt.

300
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:27,940
Gosh, that was so cool!

301
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:29,950
- How was that?
- Yes.

302
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:31,180
One more time?

303
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,880
Feel better now?

304
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,480
I'd say "not yet."

305
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:37,750
I still haven't been able
to treat the patients.

306
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:39,350
In that case,

307
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:41,690
I've got some good news for you.

308
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:46,430
You remember Chaeum Medical Group,
where you entered the cure contest?

309
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:48,100
What about them?

310
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:52,100
They donated a facility
so you can treat the patients.

311
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:53,700
They did?

312
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,910
They say you should treat the patients
in a good environment.

313
00:21:58,170 --> 00:21:59,210
That's the gist of it.

314
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:00,480
Still,

315
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:02,740
Min Seo has to get treated first.

316
00:22:04,110 --> 00:22:06,820
We've been through a lot together,

317
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:09,150
but I'm not the kind of person
who forgets that.

318
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:13,320
After all, you were the only one
who believed in me...

319
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:15,060
from the beginning.

320
00:22:18,630 --> 00:22:19,630
I was?

321
00:22:30,010 --> 00:22:31,310
(Morality)

322
00:22:37,410 --> 00:22:39,380
Remember Chaeum Medical Group?

323
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:44,220
They donated a facility
so you could treat the patients.

324
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:50,390
Your Honor, this is the cure research
Lee Woo Gyeom sent to the contest.

325
00:22:52,260 --> 00:22:56,160
At the time, his idea was highly praised
by Chaeum's research team,

326
00:22:56,230 --> 00:22:59,930
and we've confirmed that
they were even in talks to develop it.

327
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:03,770
Right, right.

328
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:07,080
- Good to see you, sir.
- That crazy...

329
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:16,220
Hey! Why are you bowing to the jerk
who stabbed you?

330
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:29,230
It must be sweltering.

331
00:23:33,340 --> 00:23:35,500
(Chaeum Medical Center)

332
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:39,910
Look...

333
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,880
Aren't you getting a little
ahead of yourself?

334
00:23:43,610 --> 00:23:47,320
What was the rush?
Why donate that facility already?

335
00:23:48,650 --> 00:23:51,990
- Because it's what the times demand.
- Chairman Chae.

336
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:56,360
It's like you're just handing the world
over to a murderer.

337
00:23:56,860 --> 00:24:01,560
Whether he's a murderer or a savior
is for the world to decide, isn't it?

338
00:24:03,430 --> 00:24:04,430
Chairman Chae!

339
00:24:28,220 --> 00:24:29,220
Old man.

340
00:24:30,090 --> 00:24:32,860
What? "Old man?"

341
00:24:33,190 --> 00:24:34,930
What do you think you're...

342
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:43,040
If you keep frowning like that,
you'll get wrinkles.

343
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:50,310
Whether Lee Woo Gyeom is convicted or not,

344
00:24:50,380 --> 00:24:53,450
all you care about is getting reelected,
isn't it?

345
00:24:55,020 --> 00:24:57,550
The seat we've helped you keep
since my father's time...

346
00:24:58,250 --> 00:24:59,250
That pin of yours.

347
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:04,190
It would be a lonely, empty life
without it, wouldn't it?

348
00:25:07,260 --> 00:25:10,330
In today's world, love is more important
than hate, and money is more important...

349
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:13,070
than power.

350
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,940
So from now on,
leave Lee Woo Gyeom alone...

351
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:20,140
and play nice.

352
00:25:20,910 --> 00:25:23,710
Let's focus on developing this cure
and saving lives, shall we?

353
00:25:24,580 --> 00:25:26,880
Do good. Make money.

354
00:25:29,450 --> 00:25:32,450
You have to behave if you don't want
some young punk walking all over you.

355
00:25:33,090 --> 00:25:34,090
Right?

356
00:25:35,590 --> 00:25:38,290
Assemblyman Baek Sang Hwa.

357
00:25:45,270 --> 00:25:48,070
(Chaeum Medical Research Institute)

358
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:51,470
(Jaeil Hospital)

359
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:53,230
Chairman Chae Jeong Su?

360
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:55,100
Yes.

361
00:26:56,040 --> 00:26:58,170
He asked me to convince Lee Woo Gyeom...

362
00:26:59,070 --> 00:27:01,080
to help them develop the cure.

363
00:27:02,140 --> 00:27:05,210
In return, he promised that
he'd let Min Seo jump the line...

364
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:10,250
and get her treated off the record.

365
00:27:13,790 --> 00:27:15,520
What are you even hesitating for?

366
00:27:16,590 --> 00:27:19,160
Right now, it's a lottery
for who gets to live or die!

367
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:24,170
Then why did you even take his case?
Look at our situation! Look at Min Seo!

368
00:27:24,670 --> 00:27:26,700
Every second counts for Min Seo!

369
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:28,770
Goodness, what are we going to do?

370
00:27:42,980 --> 00:27:43,990
Han Jun.

371
00:27:44,690 --> 00:27:48,120
Lee Woo Gyeom is the only person
on earth who can save her now.

372
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:50,490
Don't you want to save our daughter? No?

373
00:27:58,030 --> 00:27:59,230
Dad.

374
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:05,270
Daddy.

375
00:28:09,740 --> 00:28:12,080
Hey, Min Seo. You're awake.

376
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:15,550
Dad.

377
00:28:17,050 --> 00:28:18,850
Yes. You want some water?

378
00:28:21,060 --> 00:28:22,160
Dad.

379
00:28:23,990 --> 00:28:25,360
Where are you?

380
00:28:29,230 --> 00:28:30,430
I...

381
00:28:31,630 --> 00:28:32,630
My eyes...

382
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,370
They won't open.

383
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:42,840
Min Seo.

384
00:28:44,510 --> 00:28:47,980
Dad. I'm scared.

385
00:28:52,450 --> 00:28:53,450
Dad.

386
00:28:53,890 --> 00:28:54,890
Look at me.

387
00:28:57,130 --> 00:28:58,530
You really can't see me?

388
00:29:00,090 --> 00:29:04,630
No. I can't see you.

389
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:10,070
Daddy...

390
00:29:18,150 --> 00:29:19,180
Dad!

391
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:22,920
Doctor!

392
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:35,860
Here, drink up.

393
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:40,170
Isn't this a little cheap
for a farewell gift?

394
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:43,100
It's to energize you for work.

395
00:29:44,470 --> 00:29:46,540
Work on what? The trial's over.

396
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:48,410
You remember the look...

397
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:50,010
on Prosecutor Cha's face
when the verdict was read?

398
00:29:50,650 --> 00:29:51,850
How could I forget?

399
00:29:52,180 --> 00:29:54,980
She looked like she wanted
to murder our boss.

400
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:59,390
Knowing her, she's collecting evidence
to overturn the Supreme Court's ruling...

401
00:29:59,450 --> 00:30:00,760
and will file for a retrial
immediately, I bet.

402
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:04,390
Besides, let's be honest.

403
00:30:04,860 --> 00:30:07,630
Lee Woo Gyeom only just dodged
the death penalty.

404
00:30:08,230 --> 00:30:10,530
And his relationship with Professor Han
is still a little murky.

405
00:30:10,970 --> 00:30:15,940
And they still haven't found the killer
of Song Min Su, Professor Han's colleague.

406
00:30:17,210 --> 00:30:20,480
And another thing,
what about all that money...

407
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,540
that Chaeum Medical Group
is suddenly giving...

408
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:25,310
to support Lee Woo Gyeom?
Don't you think that's weird?

409
00:30:25,510 --> 00:30:27,920
That's where Professor Han and Song Min Su
used to work together.

410
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:32,390
You're right. It's pretty weird,
almost as weird as you.

411
00:30:33,050 --> 00:30:37,490
My dear Min Jung is
such a bad judge of character. My gosh.

412
00:30:38,860 --> 00:30:42,860
My judgment's better than someone's memory
who's gotten my name wrong 12 times.

413
00:30:42,930 --> 00:30:46,000
Goodness. You kept count? Twelve times?

414
00:30:46,730 --> 00:30:49,370
Smart and spunky Min Jung.

415
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:52,210
You're ready to get back to work.

416
00:30:54,010 --> 00:30:57,040
And that's why
I've prepared a little something.

417
00:30:57,450 --> 00:31:00,410
Ta-da!

418
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:04,220
Let's work together on a special feature
about Lee Woo Gyeom.

419
00:31:04,690 --> 00:31:07,990
His entire life story, from birth to now.

420
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:13,800
I figure it's the perfect way to clear up
all the mysteries surrounding him, right?

421
00:31:15,330 --> 00:31:18,000
This will rake in a ton of ad money.

422
00:31:18,470 --> 00:31:20,970
And I'll give you a cut.

423
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:26,610
If you don't want to, you can just go back
to the press club and keep making copies.

424
00:31:26,770 --> 00:31:29,440
No, that's not what I meant.

425
00:31:30,340 --> 00:31:31,910
So what's the split?

426
00:31:33,820 --> 00:31:35,350
The split...
I haven't really thought about it.

427
00:31:36,620 --> 00:31:37,620
Ninety-ten?

428
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:39,750
Take your coffee back.

429
00:31:39,820 --> 00:31:43,720
Gosh, so it's all about the money, right?
Fine. Eighty-twenty. No, seventy-thirty.

430
00:31:43,790 --> 00:31:45,030
Seventy-thirty sounds fair, doesn't it?

431
00:31:45,390 --> 00:31:48,500
- It is a perfectly fair split.
- A little higher.

432
00:31:48,860 --> 00:31:50,670
- Fifty-fifty?
- Fifty-fifty. You got a deal!

433
00:31:50,730 --> 00:31:52,770
Deal! All right, look.

434
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:53,970
(The Prosecution)

435
00:31:55,570 --> 00:31:59,170
(Attorney Cha Yi Yeon)

436
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:06,480
(Notice of case disposition)

437
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:08,750
Professor Han Sang Ho.

438
00:32:09,420 --> 00:32:14,090
Due to illegal human experiments
conducted without the victims' consent...

439
00:32:15,090 --> 00:32:18,090
led to a chain of victims.

440
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:23,460
Are you also aware that Professor Han
used Lee Woo Gyeom as a test subject?

441
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:36,180
The ones who cleared Professor Han
of all charges...

442
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:39,150
They are Director Oh Hyeon Deuk
and Assemblyman Baek Sang Hwa.

443
00:32:39,210 --> 00:32:40,620
(Oh Hyeon Deuk, Baek Sang Hwa)

444
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,680
Before you found out, Prosecutor...

445
00:32:43,020 --> 00:32:48,220
What's important is that someone already
handled everything with Lee Woo Gyeom.

446
00:32:48,860 --> 00:32:52,730
If there's someone
pulling the strings behind them,

447
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:56,230
- that would mean...
- If you dig too deep,

448
00:32:56,730 --> 00:33:01,170
- you could get hurt, Prosecutor.
- Who could it be?

449
00:33:01,970 --> 00:33:02,970
Prosecutor Cha.

450
00:33:05,210 --> 00:33:06,240
Prosecutor Cha.

451
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,880
We'll be on our way.

452
00:33:13,780 --> 00:33:15,420
Where are you being transferred to?

453
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:20,590
For now, I'll work for Prosecutor Lee
in the Acting Prosecutor's Office.

454
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:24,530
Thank you both for all your hard work.

455
00:33:29,460 --> 00:33:30,870
- Let's go.
- Okay.

456
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:38,640
Prosecutor Cha.

457
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:43,340
If you look at the bottom of
Professor Han Sang Ho's file,

458
00:33:43,610 --> 00:33:45,850
I've organized some additional information
I found.

459
00:33:46,650 --> 00:33:47,650
Thank you.

460
00:33:48,220 --> 00:33:49,980
Stay in touch, Prosecutor Cha.

461
00:33:51,890 --> 00:33:53,120
Thank you for your hard work.

462
00:33:58,890 --> 00:33:59,890
Okay.

463
00:34:17,410 --> 00:34:18,410
What is it now?

464
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:20,410
You still have more to say?

465
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:24,050
You know that Professor Han Sang Ho is
connected to Lee Woo Gyeom, don't you?

466
00:34:24,820 --> 00:34:26,390
Tell me what you know.

467
00:34:29,220 --> 00:34:30,260
Know when to quit.

468
00:34:31,130 --> 00:34:32,930
Tell me what your relationship
with him was.

469
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:37,130
Does your father know
you're acting this way?

470
00:34:38,330 --> 00:34:39,500
The trial is over,

471
00:34:40,100 --> 00:34:41,300
so why are you still dredging this up?

472
00:34:41,870 --> 00:34:45,610
Don't even think about a retrial.
Just lay low for a month, then disappear.

473
00:34:46,740 --> 00:34:47,740
This is your last warning.

474
00:35:03,120 --> 00:35:05,360
It seems Prosecutor Cha
is on Professor Han's trail as well.

475
00:35:09,230 --> 00:35:10,900
And where is Professor Han now?

476
00:35:12,330 --> 00:35:13,470
We're still looking for him.

477
00:35:24,010 --> 00:35:25,380
"We're still looking for him?"

478
00:35:31,020 --> 00:35:33,290
I don't want, "We're looking for him."
I want to hear, "We've found him."

479
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:36,590
That's what you should be reporting to me.

480
00:35:37,830 --> 00:35:38,830
I apologize.

481
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:44,430
I need you to bring me answers,
not more problems.

482
00:35:44,830 --> 00:35:46,770
Even as we speak,
because of incurable diseases,

483
00:35:46,770 --> 00:35:49,400
countless patients are tragically dying,
aren't they?

484
00:35:50,540 --> 00:35:51,610
Director Ahn.

485
00:35:55,740 --> 00:35:57,780
For the sake of the patients
and their families,

486
00:35:57,850 --> 00:36:01,280
don't you think we need to succeed
in developing this cure quickly?

487
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:04,090
Yes, you're right, sir.

488
00:36:04,590 --> 00:36:05,820
Please hurry.

489
00:36:07,090 --> 00:36:08,090
Yes, sir.

490
00:36:15,230 --> 00:36:16,230
Right.

491
00:36:18,170 --> 00:36:20,130
He doesn't need to be breathing, does he?

492
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:23,770
- Sir?
- I'm talking about Professor Han.

493
00:36:26,740 --> 00:36:28,410
Yes, I understand.

494
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:45,460
(Chelsea Hotel)

495
00:38:07,910 --> 00:38:09,280
In the new drug development project,

496
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:12,450
isn't two-percent for Assemblyman Baek
a little excessive?

497
00:38:16,420 --> 00:38:19,020
Assemblyman Baek also saw Lee Woo Gyeom
as a thorn in his side.

498
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,090
Just consider it an investment
in the future.

499
00:38:22,820 --> 00:38:23,820
Are you sure about this?

500
00:38:24,490 --> 00:38:27,190
He was on TV last time,
shooting his mouth off.

501
00:38:28,060 --> 00:38:31,230
I think we should've taken this chance
to replace him with some new blood.

502
00:38:33,430 --> 00:38:34,500
Don't worry.

503
00:38:34,900 --> 00:38:37,370
You've never lost money on Chaeum,
have you?

504
00:38:37,870 --> 00:38:41,010
Did you forget the plan was to launch
the new drug last year?

505
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:44,380
You're the one who broke your promise
in the first place.

506
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:46,950
But with Lee Woo Gyeom,

507
00:38:46,950 --> 00:38:49,080
it's just a matter of time
until the treatment is ready.

508
00:38:49,420 --> 00:38:52,090
- We can discuss Mr. Baek's seat later...
- Chairman Chae.

509
00:38:53,650 --> 00:38:57,630
Don't tell me this is happening
because you got involved with Mr. Baek.

510
00:38:58,490 --> 00:38:59,490
Excuse me?

511
00:39:02,260 --> 00:39:03,500
Me, get involved with someone?

512
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,600
Who are you suggesting?

513
00:39:11,270 --> 00:39:12,340
Madam Chairman.

514
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:17,440
You have to feed the dog
if you want it to hunt.

515
00:39:18,650 --> 00:39:20,780
I am his master, after all.
So how could I...

516
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:23,520
let him starve to death?

517
00:39:30,790 --> 00:39:32,460
Everyone, let's stop
with the pointless worrying...

518
00:39:33,390 --> 00:39:35,260
and focus on what's important.

519
00:39:36,730 --> 00:39:37,730
Got it?

520
00:39:58,150 --> 00:39:59,350
- It's Park Han Jun!
- It's Park Han Jun!

521
00:40:00,950 --> 00:40:03,590
Mr. Park, what's your reaction
to the verdict?

522
00:40:05,130 --> 00:40:07,460
- Sorry.
- Still in contact with Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom?

523
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:10,130
Is it true you only defended him
to get treatment for your daughter?

524
00:40:11,030 --> 00:40:12,430
Ladies and gentlemen of the press.

525
00:40:13,770 --> 00:40:15,970
We declined an interview,
so if you report on this...

526
00:40:16,270 --> 00:40:19,340
You're aware you'll be sued for
invasion of privacy, right?

527
00:40:22,810 --> 00:40:23,810
The Namhae Prosecutor's Office?

528
00:40:26,750 --> 00:40:28,050
You're headed somewhere
with nice country air. I see.

529
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:29,820
You think this is funny?

530
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,290
And whose fault do you think that is?

531
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:36,120
That's why I told you
not to trust Chief Oh.

532
00:40:36,420 --> 00:40:38,030
I never trusted him.

533
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:43,200
In what world does an employee
get to choose their boss?

534
00:40:45,470 --> 00:40:46,470
Nowhere.

535
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:51,670
Are you kidding me right now?

536
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,910
Look, you know Professor Han Sang Ho,
right?

537
00:40:59,110 --> 00:41:02,220
I'm Lee Woo Gyeom's lawyer.
Of course I know him.

538
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:06,850
There's a past case that connects
Professor Han to Chief Oh,

539
00:41:07,620 --> 00:41:08,660
and something's off about it.

540
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:11,890
And why are you telling me this now?

541
00:41:12,730 --> 00:41:14,700
Are you blowing me off
now that the trial is over?

542
00:41:15,430 --> 00:41:18,100
Look, I'm a lawyer, not a detective.

543
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:26,570
Then what if Lee Woo Gyeom
is involved in this case too?

544
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:42,990
(Minister of Health and Welfare
Park Jun Jae...)

545
00:41:43,060 --> 00:41:44,560
(Announces Patient Selection by Lottery)

546
00:41:52,470 --> 00:41:54,270
They're selecting patients by lottery?

547
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:58,040
What? Does that even make sense?
Imagine how many people will apply.

548
00:41:58,310 --> 00:42:00,710
- They mean Lee Woo Gyeom, right?
- Looks like it.

549
00:42:03,340 --> 00:42:08,050
(Interview: Dr. Han Sang Ho)

550
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,220
(Jinnam Medical Research Institute)

551
00:42:16,420 --> 00:42:21,130
Illegal human experiments conducted
without the subjects' consent...

552
00:42:22,130 --> 00:42:25,330
resulted in a series of adverse events.

553
00:42:25,730 --> 00:42:28,100
(Lottery Selection and Treatment Support:
Chaeum Medical Center)

554
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:36,980
- Hey, it's me.
- What are we going to do? Our Min Seo...

555
00:42:49,260 --> 00:42:50,360
(Treatment Recipient Management Chart)

556
00:42:55,530 --> 00:42:57,760
(Oh Seo Jun, Yoon Ha Neul, Jang Seo Hyun,
Noh Eun Woo, Baek Min Ji)

557
00:42:57,900 --> 00:42:59,500
(Hwang Da On, Seo Chae Hyun,
Jo Ah Young, Im Tae Eun)

558
00:42:59,570 --> 00:43:00,930
(Jeong Na Ri, Song Ji Su, Han Eun Chae)

559
00:43:01,440 --> 00:43:03,640
Park Min Seo... Why isn't she on the list?

560
00:43:17,650 --> 00:43:18,690
Jae Hee!

561
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:23,160
(Intensive Care Unit)

562
00:43:25,330 --> 00:43:27,660
Hey... Where's our Min Seo?

563
00:43:31,900 --> 00:43:33,230
What's going to happen to our Min Seo?

564
00:43:39,640 --> 00:43:42,880
(Intensive Care Unit)

565
00:43:50,750 --> 00:43:53,050
(Chae Jeong Su)

566
00:43:58,060 --> 00:44:01,260
It's a pleasure to finally meet you.
Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon.

567
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:38,900
Have you been well?

568
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:51,880
Administer a little more medication.

569
00:44:52,580 --> 00:44:53,580
Vitals are...

570
00:44:58,450 --> 00:45:00,150
The vitals are irregular.

571
00:45:05,360 --> 00:45:08,830
Professor Han Sang Ho?
Yes, of course I know him.

572
00:45:09,460 --> 00:45:14,000
My father, the former chairman,
personally recruited him back in 2015.

573
00:45:14,070 --> 00:45:18,440
They worked together until 2023,
when he resigned for personal reasons.

574
00:45:18,770 --> 00:45:20,010
By your father, you mean...

575
00:45:20,510 --> 00:45:25,180
- the renowned expert on stem cells...
- Yes. That's Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

576
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,180
He and Professor Han were friends,

577
00:45:28,350 --> 00:45:31,650
and the two of them devoted themselves
to studying incurable diseases at Chaeum.

578
00:45:38,290 --> 00:45:40,260
Mr. Ahn.

579
00:45:41,330 --> 00:45:42,760
I'm sorry, but could you give us a moment?

580
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:53,040
How have you been?

581
00:45:55,410 --> 00:45:57,210
Just a bit boring, that's all.

582
00:46:01,010 --> 00:46:02,350
Everything's ready to go, right?

583
00:46:21,740 --> 00:46:23,770
(Intensive Care Unit)

584
00:46:29,580 --> 00:46:31,210
Now the seizures will get more frequent,

585
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:34,210
and dementia will start to set in.

586
00:46:34,920 --> 00:46:38,190
As the symptoms progress,
her life expectancy will shorten.

587
00:46:39,250 --> 00:46:42,420
I think it's best to prepare yourselves.

588
00:46:45,660 --> 00:46:47,930
(Intensive Care Unit)

589
00:47:01,140 --> 00:47:02,140
Min Seo.

590
00:47:02,640 --> 00:47:03,640
Min Seo.

591
00:47:05,050 --> 00:47:06,710
Min Seo.

592
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,120
Min Seo.

593
00:47:12,420 --> 00:47:16,020
You're curious about the malpractice case
involving Professor Han, aren't you?

594
00:47:20,590 --> 00:47:23,060
You're on official business.
Please, ask any questions, Prosecutor.

595
00:47:25,700 --> 00:47:28,600
Since you're being so cooperative
about a closed case,

596
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:30,940
I'll be frank with you.

597
00:47:32,540 --> 00:47:35,240
The charges were dropped
due to a lack of evidence,

598
00:47:35,780 --> 00:47:38,680
but is it true that
Professor Han Sang Ho...

599
00:47:39,410 --> 00:47:40,880
conducted human experiments
without subjects' consent...

600
00:47:41,650 --> 00:47:44,480
at the Chaeum Medical Research Center?

601
00:47:58,700 --> 00:48:00,670
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
